    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Style of Nubian fresco and panel painting that, among other stylistic characteristics, uses the color white more than had previous styles; it dated from the end of 11th century until around 1175.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000050876/Moorsel, et al, Central Church of Abdallah Nirqi (1975)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Stijl van Nubische fresco- en paneelschilderstijlen die als een van de stilistische kenmerken had dat hij meer gebruikmaakte van de kleur wit dan eerdere stijlen. De stijl ontstond aan het einde van de 11e eeuw en bleef bestaan tot ongeveer 1175.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>努比亞壁畫與鑲板油畫的風格，在其他風格特徵中，其在白色的運用上較之前的風格多。該風格可溯源於11世紀末，至大約西元1175年。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
